parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to serious injury or death in the event of an accident, as the airbags may not deploy properly or at all.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated on the dashboard
the airbag light turns on and off
the airbags do not deploy in the event of an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay or refusal to repair recalled vehicles can lead to continued safety risks for drivers and passengers, as well as potential accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Dealerships or manufacturers fail to provide recall repairs in a timely manner
dealerships or manufacturers claim parts are not available
dealerships or manufacturers show a lack of concern or knowledge about recall repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Uncertainty about the status of outstanding recalls can lead to concerns about vehicle safety and potential risks to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: difficulty obtaining information about recall repairs
uncertainty about whether recall repairs have been completed.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Water Accumulation and Rust on Front Passenger Side Floor
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water accumulation on the front passenger side floor can lead to rust and corrosion, compromising the structural integrity of the vehicle and potentially causing electrical system failures.
symptoms: Water pooling on the front passenger side floor
rust or corrosion on the floor or surrounding components
musty odor or water damage inside the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Improper drainage of air conditioner condensate can cause water to accumulate inside the vehicle, leading to rust, corrosion, and electrical system failures.
symptoms: Water accumulation on the front passenger side floor
rust or corrosion on the floor or surrounding components
musty odor or water damage inside the vehicle.
